{
  "content": "---\nlayout: null\n---\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"UTF-8\">\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n  <title>BLOG — NEXUS ROOT LAB</title>\n  <meta name=\"description\" content=\"Security research blog — kernel exploitation, vulnerability analysis, and systems security.\">\n  <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com\">\n  <link rel=\"preconnect\" href=\"https://fonts.gstatic.com\" crossorigin>\n  <link href=\"https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=IBM+Plex+Mono:wght@400;500;600&family=Rajdhani:wght@400;600;700&display=swap\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.1/css/all.min.css\">\n  <link rel=\"stylesheet\" href=\"/css/style.css\">\n</head>\n<body id=\"top\">\n\n  <!-- Scanline overlay -->\n  <div class=\"scanline-overlay\" aria-hidden=\"true\"></div>\n\n  <!-- Navigation -->\n  <nav class=\"nav-main\" role=\"navigation\" aria-label=\"Main navigation\">\n    <div class=\"nav-inner\">\n      <a href=\"/\" class=\"nav-logo\" aria-label=\"Nexus Root Lab home\">\n        <svg viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M12 2L2 7l10 5 10-5-10-5zM2 17l10 5 10-5M2 12l10 5 10-5\"/></svg>\n        NEXUS ROOT LAB\n      </a>\n      <div class=\"nav-links\">\n        <a href=\"/#about\" class=\"nav-link\">About</a>\n        <a href=\"/#projects\" class=\"nav-link\">Projects</a>\n        <a href=\"/blog/\" class=\"nav-link active\">Blog</a>\n        <a href=\"/#contact\" class=\"nav-link\">Contact</a>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </nav>\n\n  <!-- Blog Header -->\n  <section class=\"section\" style=\"padding-top: calc(56px + var(--space-3xl));\">\n    <div class=\"container\">\n      <div class=\"section-label\">// /var/log/research</div>\n      <h1 class=\"section-title\">Research Log</h1>\n      <hr class=\"divider\">\n\n      <!-- Blog Grid -->\n      <div class=\"blog-grid\">\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-12-15\">2024.12.15</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">8 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/ebpf-rootkit-detection/\">eBPF-Based Rootkit Detection in Modern Kernels</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Exploring how eBPF program verification can be leveraged to detect malicious kernel modules and rootkit persistence mechanisms in real-time.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">eBPF</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Linux</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Detection</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-11-28\">2024.11.28</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">12 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/firmware-supply-chain/\">Firmware Supply Chain Attacks: A Practical Analysis</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Case study on firmware supply chain compromise vectors in embedded devices. Analysis of three real-world incidents and defensive countermeasures.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">Firmware</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Supply Chain</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-10-03\">2024.10.03</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">6 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/rop-chain-evolution/\">The Evolution of ROP Chains Post-RET</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">From classical ROP to JOP and COP: tracing the evolution of code-reuse attacks and the never-ending arms race with control-flow integrity defenses.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">Exploitation</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">ROP</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Mitigation</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-09-19\">2024.09.19</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">10 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/confidential-computing-attack-surface/\">Attack Surface of Confidential Computing Enclaves</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Mapping the trust boundaries and attack surfaces of TEE implementations — from SGX to ARM TrustZone and emerging RISC-V enclaves.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">TEE</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">SGX</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Hardware</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-08-05\">2024.08.05</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">7 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/rust-memory-safety/\">Can Rust Save Us? A Realistic Look at Memory Safety</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Examining the actual security impact of Rust adoption in systems code — beyond the hype, looking at CVE data and real-world exploitability reductions.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">Rust</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Memory Safety</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Analysis</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-07-22\">2024.07.22</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">9 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/covert-channel-taxonomy/\">A Taxonomy of Network Covert Channels</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Systematic classification of covert communication methods — timing channels, storage channels, and protocol manipulation techniques for C2 evasion.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">Covert Channels</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Networking</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">C2</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-06-10\">2024.06.10</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">5 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/bpf-bypass-techniques/\">BPF Verifier Bypass Techniques: A Survey</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">Cataloging known techniques for bypassing the eBPF verifier — from Spectre-based primitives to type confusion in map operations.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">eBPF</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Exploitation</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Kernel</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n        <article class=\"blog-card\">\n          <div class=\"blog-meta\">\n            <time class=\"blog-date\" datetime=\"2024-05-01\">2024.05.01</time>\n            <span class=\"blog-read-time\">11 min</span>\n          </div>\n          <h3><a href=\"/blog/posts/dma-attacks-resurgence/\">The Resurgence of DMA Attacks in the Thunderbolt Era</a></h3>\n          <p class=\"blog-excerpt\">How USB4 and Thunderbolt 4 have reopened direct memory access attack vectors, and why IOMMU configurations still fail in practice.</p>\n          <div class=\"blog-tags\">\n            <span class=\"tag\">DMA</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Hardware</span>\n            <span class=\"tag\">Thunderbolt</span>\n          </div>\n        </article>\n\n       